{
  "doc_id": "53377",
  "text": "A total of 930 individuals were included in the study: 467 BD, 393 UCPP, and 70 PGP ( Figure 1 ). The characteristics of the three groups are presented in Table A1 . The sample size was calculated according to previously described methods [CITATION_1] . A sample size of 384 was calculated assuming an a priori 50% anti-HEV seroprevalence, a confidence in the estimate of 95%, a maximum allowable error in the prevalence of 5%, and a Corsican population size of 330,455 habitants (based on the latest French census data).",
